From 68e36be21a6535c652998f6adc58e07b11eed2ed Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 20:21:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add exponential pitch sweep and transient click layer
 (milestone 4)

Pitch:
- Replace linear-in-Hz pitch interpolation with an exponential (log-domain)
  sweep: freq = start * (end/start)^(t^curve). Pitch is perceived as ratios,
  so this removes the "floaty" low-end glide the design report warns about.
  The waveform preview uses the same formula.

Transient:
- New dsp/noise.rs: allocation-free xorshift32 white-noise source.
- New biquad high-pass mode (set_highpass) to shape the click.
- A dedicated short click envelope, triggered alongside the main envelopes.
- The click is mixed in parallel AFTER the distortion (mixdown-after routing)
  so it keeps its mechanical "tok" definition.
- New params: click_level (default 0 = silent), click_decay, click_tone.
- New TRANSIENT section in the editor.

Refactor:
- Consolidate all triggering into HardKick::fire(), used by both the immediate
  and post-declick paths, so the pitch/amp/click envelopes stay in sync.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
